team6.finalproject

Class ObjectSearch

  • java.lang.Object
    • team6.finalproject.ObjectSearch

  • public class ObjectSearch
extends java.lang.Object
    Class that scans the field for objects and determines if objects are to be avoided or if they are to be collected.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Andrei Ungur, Erick Zhao

    • Method Detail

      • doSearch

        public void doSearch()
        Implements all the elements of the search into an algorithm. Performs a sweep and moves to next neighbourhood. Runs for 4 minutes and returns to starting point.

      • bringToEndzone

        public void bringToEndzone(double x,
                           double y)
        Travels from the current position to the middle of the end zone (green or red depending on which mode the robot is in).
        Parameters:
        x - middle of endzone's x position
        y - middle of endzone's y position

      • sweep

        public void sweep()
        Sweeps the current neighborhood by rotating about a point, keeping track of if objects are detected in the neighborhood

      • travelToWaypoint

        public void travelToWaypoint(int wayPoint)
        Moves the robot to the starting point for the next neighborhood to scan
        Parameters:
        wayPoint - the int coordinate for start of next neighborhood to scan

      • handleBlock

        public void handleBlock(boolean pickUp)
        Grasps a styrofoam block with the claw if "pickUp" is true. Releasses styrofoam block if "pickUp" is false.
